<div id="sub-main" >
	<div id="wiki-content-block">

	
		


<p><strong>Twinkling Dragon Torso Stone</strong> is a <a class="wiki_link" href="/Tools">Tool</a>&nbsp;in Dark Souls 3.</p> 
<div id="infobox" class="infobox"> 
 <div class="table-responsive"> 
  <table class="wiki_table"> 
   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;"> <h3>Twinkling Dragon Torso Stone</h3> </td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/file/Dark-Souls-3/twinkling_dragon_stone_torso.png" alt="" width="100"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td><br> 
      <blockquote> 
       <p>Stone imbued with the power of the everlasting dragons, offered to a towering dragon. This stone shows signs of a nascent light.<br><br>Gain the torso of a dragon and roar alongside an archdragon mirage. The transformation is irreversible until death.<br><br>Yet true imitation will require a dragon head, as well.</p> 
      </blockquote> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 id="toc0" class="bonfire"><a name="x--Green Blossom Usage"></a>Twinkling Dragon Torso Stone Usage</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Gain dragon torso until death Must remove all armor to use; Head, Chest, Arm, and Leg armor.</li> 
 <li>Reactivating the stone boosts attack damage for 5 seconds 
  <ul> 
   <li>PVE = + 10% AR</li> 
   <li>PVP = additional modifier = 1.125*damage</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>Summons dragon arms in front of player character that crush enemies</li> 
 <li>Attribute bonus of D for Intelligence and C for Faith</li> 
 <li>Once the player is in dragon form, they gain&nbsp;elemental absorptions (except for lightning). The exact gains are:&nbsp;Magic and Dark absorption by 16.48, Fire absorption by 32.66,&nbsp;but <strong>reduces</strong> lightning absorption by 15.44. It also increases all Resistances by 60.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 id="toc1" class="bonfire"><a name="x--Green Blossom Locations"></a>Twinkling Dragon Torso Stone Location</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Located at the very end of <a class="wiki_link" href="/Archdragon+Peak">Archdragon Peak</a> by using the "Path of the Dragon" on the altar.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div id="https://www.youtube.com/embed/sQS0CK1owLs?list=PLyT5NcCVqdX9o2nRq4WehERfn2k-7vAqg" class="embed-responsive-item youtube-item" style="display: flex; justify-content: center;"> 
 <div class="sk-cube-grid" style="display: block; margin: auto;"> 
